Demonstration of Buffered send operation.

For that we need to allocate a buffer. The buffer can be allocated per group,
per session, and per process. Here we use `MPI_Buffer_attach` to allocate
memory. Later on we can get detach the buffer and get the handle/ptr to the
allocated memory, along with its size back.

    MPI_Buffer_detach(buffer_addr, size)
        - OUT buffer addr initial buffer address (choice)
        - OUT size buffer size, in bytes (integer)

    > Detach the MPI process-specific buffer buffer currently attached to MPI

    NOTE:
        the buffer space is not available for reuse by subsequent `MPI_Bsend`s
        unless you are certain that the message has been received (not just
        that it should have been received).

    NOTE:
        MPI_BSEND_OVERHEAD:
            Add this to the size of a MPI_BSEND buffer for each outstanding
            message.
